# Update Profile Section & Add Profile Summary Page

The goal is to prefetch data from the database to fill in the necessary fields in the profile setup wizard. Furthermore, a single-page profile summary screen will be added, displaying essential user details (social media, name, bio, etc.) which fits on one screen and allows navigating back to the setup form to edit those fields. The new summary screen will be styled to match the dark, dramatic aesthetic (e.g., toxic green, electric magenta, cold blue, and molten gold) matching the `StitchMCP` prompt and your overarching visual requirements.

## Proposed Changes

### Dashboard Profile Component

#### [NEW] `j:/PaceUp/app/dashboard/profile/page.tsx`
Create a new Server Component that acts as the user's profile summary page.
- Validates if the user is authenticated and fetches their data from the database.
- If `profileData` does not exist, redirects the user to `/dashboard/profile/setup`.
- Displays the user's name, headline, bio, location, education, current role, and a row of social media links.
- Uses dynamic design elements in sync with the project's aesthetic (e.g., `bg-bg-tertiary`, neon accents, glow pulses).
- Includes an "Edit Profile" button that securely redirects to `/dashboard/profile/setup`.

### Profile Setup Components

#### [MODIFY] `j:/PaceUp/app/dashboard/profile/setup/page.tsx`
Refactor this file from a Client Component to a React Server Component.
- Fetch the user's data from the DB using `getOrCreateUser(clerkId)`.
- If the user has existing `profileData`, pass this information as `initialData` to a new Client Component to ensure the inputs are pre-filled upon visit.

#### [NEW] `j:/PaceUp/app/dashboard/profile/setup/profile-setup-client.tsx`
Extract the client-side wizard logic from the current `setup/page.tsx`.
- Accept an optional `initialData` prop.
- Merge the `initialData` with the `INITIAL_FORM_STATE` to pre-populate all form fields correctly.
- Retain all form validation, transition animations, and patch requests just like before.

